# CineLog 🎬

A modern movie rating and watchlist platform built with .NET and The Movie Database (TMDb) API.

## Features ✨

- 🔐 **JWT Authentication** - Secure user registration and login
- 🎬 **Movie Database Integration** - Real movie data from TMDb API
- ⭐ **Movie Rating System** - Rate and review your favorite films
- 📝 **Personal Watchlists** - Track what you want to watch
- 👥 **User Profiles** - Manage your movie preferences
- 🏗️ **Clean Architecture** - Maintainable, testable, and scalable code

## Technology Stack 🛠️

- **.NET 9** - Latest .NET framework
- **ASP.NET Core Web API** - RESTful API backend
- **Entity Framework Core** - ORM with PostgreSQL
- **PostgreSQL** - Production-ready database
- **JWT Bearer Authentication** - Secure token-based auth
- **Swagger/OpenAPI** - Interactive API documentation
- **TMDb API** - The Movie Database integration

## Architecture 🏛️

This project follows **Clean Architecture** principles with clear separation of concerns:
├── CineLog.Core/          # Business logic and domain entities
├── CineLog.Infrastructure/ # Data access and external services
├── CineLog.API/           # Web API controllers and configuration
└── CineLog.Tests/         # Unit and integration tests

## Getting Started 🚀

### Prerequisites

- .NET 9 SDK
- PostgreSQL
- TMDb API Key

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/CineLog.git
   cd CineLog
   
2. Set up configuration
   cp CineLog.API/appsettings.example.json CineLog.API/appsettings.json
	
	# Edit appsettings.json with your database and API keys

3. Run database migrations
	dotnet ef database update --project CineLog.Infrastructure --startup-project CineLog.API

4. Run the application
	dotnet run --project CineLog.API
	
5. Open Swagger UI
	Navigate to https://localhost:5003/swagger
	
	POST /api/auth/register - User registration
	POST /api/auth/login - User login
	GET /api/auth/me - Get current user info
	GET /api/movies/search - Search movies
	GET /api/movies/trending - Get trending movies
	GET /api/movies/{id} - Get movie details

